review_blob: Tan head not lasting, clear reddish brown color, sweet grape malt aromas, watery  smooth with sutle carbonation, smooth watery feel, weet malty flavor with  a wine like finish, surprisingly suble change sherry like as it warmed.

Tan head light, clear bronze copper color, sweet malt aroma, soft slippery  mouth feel, soft carbonation, malt flavors, with a bit of hops on the finish, benign for a douple IPA, fairly strong liquor like finish that got stronger as it warmed
beer_name: Ass Kisser Royal Donk Double IPA

review_blob: white dininishing head, clear copper color, pumpkin and spice aromas, nice smooth mouth feel, very well balanced, rich pumpkin flavor with a mild alcohol warmth on the finish.
Off whtie diminishing head, pours a clear amber, lemon and spice aroma, spice and wheat taste, very smooth.
Tan head, very ligth and gone fast, sweet caramel malt aroma, deep red mahogany brown, sweet caramel and roasted malt flaovor.

Bottled pours a nice rich amber orange, light white head, spice and cinnamon pumpkin aroma, very nice pumpkin and spice flavor, spice on the finish, decent but pretty sweet.
Golden, cloudy, white foam, spice and lemon aroma, lemon and coriander on the flavor, clean finish.
Tan head one finger slowly dissipates, roasted chocolate aroma and nuts, dark mahogany color, soft carbonation, thin feel, roasted burnt coffee flavor with a dark chocolate maltiness.
Pale yellow, thin white diminishing head, not much going on a step above tonic water.

Pours a clear golden amber color, light white head, sweet malt aroma with some floral notes, lively carbonation, sweet flavor with a raw alcohol taste to it, more alcohol on the finish, slick mouth feel with medium body, get the warm alcohol on the finish.
Clear amber, off white head, light malt aroma. very easy drink very plain malt flavor not much top say about it.
Bottle pours a nice orange bronze color with a tan head that lasts, sweet roasted malts,  burnt smoke aromas, a bit of hops on the finish, watery mouth feel.
Bottle pours black, black, hearty tan head that lasts, sweet molasses aroma, rich roasted coffee flavor, smooth nice carbonation, some alcohol on the finish.
Sampler,clear dark brown, tan head, coffee on the finish, syrupy mouth fee, roasted malt aromas, a taste of hops on the finishl
Sampler, nice dark amber color, of white head, sweet malt aroma, some hops on the finish, smooth good balance, flavor sweet malts to hops with a bit of toast and honey.
Sampler fruit note, light white head, smooth mouth feel, clear red raspberry color that flavor follows into the palate, decent fruit beer.
Sampler off white head, clear golden color with strong lacing, soft carbonation, sweet malt aroma that follows into the flavor, smooth and real soft mouth feel.
Sampler Cloudy amber with a white head, clove and fruits aroma, faint hop hit on the finish, soft carbonation.
Sampler, pale yellow, malt and lemon aroma, light white head that vanishes, light lemon flavor with some sweet malts, watery mouth feel, smooth and light, just not a lot to it.j

review_blob: Pours a pale gold with an off white head, hoppy smell, very smooth and light, hops taste, nice sweet malt with a light hop flavor, very nice smooth finish with a touch of hop bitter, smooth mouth feel.
Pours a burgundy color, with a nice tan head, soft carbonation, bit of a coffee and chocolate notes, some sweet malts, watery mouth feel.
Pours a golden amber, white head, hoppy flavor, smooth mouth feel, hop bitters on the finish, not bad though, mild carbonation.
Cloudy very pale yellow, soft carbonation, lemon and yeast aroma, lemon on the finish, very mild and easy drink.
Clear pale yellow on the pour, sweet aroma with some lemon, watery mouth feel, light lemony wheat taste with a white head.
Clear gold in color, white head, nice lacing, aroma not much, slight hop kick on the finish, smooth watery mouth feel.

Pours a deep reddish brown, little to no tan head last gone quickly, sweet malt aromas, roasted malt flavor with some chocolate and coffee notes, smooths out as it warms, mild carbonation, bit of soft bitterness on the finish, fairly well balanced though.
Bottled pours jet black, light brown head, with roasted coffee aroma, roasted coffee flavor with bourbon and alcohol, thick syrupy mouth feel, coffee after taste
bottled, pumpkin pie aroma light white head not lasting, a clear golden orange color, nice pumpkin flavor with real nice spice notes as it warms.

Bottle pours black, chocolate brown head, malty aroma, soft light carbonation, coffee flavor, smooth mouth feel, very easy ddrinkng stout

2 finger off white head lasting, dark golden brown, sweet caramel aromas , with a roasted malt flavor, sweet honey with a hint of bourbon on the finish, slippery mouth feel nice, mellower as it warms with a soft carbonation

Off white head, lasting, nice lacing. Cloudy pale yellowish orange.  Floral aroma with light carbonation.  Very smooth very light taste really refreshing, nice wheat with a touch of lemon and spice.   Enjoyed this one.

Bottled pours black, tan 1/2 finger head quickly dissipates, sweet roasted malt aroma, light mouth feel, roasted malts, chocolate and coffee, quick alcohol finish.

Bottle, pours black with 2 finger chocolate milk colored head, lasting, sweet malty smell, soft mouth feel, light carbonation, roasted smoked malty flavor with a touch of hoppy bitterness on the finish,

pours a deep cloudy brown, nice lasting tan head, sweet yeasty aroma, watery smooth drink, nothing jumps out taste wise, soft wheat taste. eye catching bottle but noth9ng jumps out at you taste wise, very soft smooth finish.
Light tan 2 finger head mostly lasting, reddish brown, cloudy, sweet spicy caramel aroma, soft mouth feel, smooth blend of sweet and hops not bitter, soft mouth feel with moderate carbonation

Pours black with a light 1 finger tan head that lingers, nice chocolate roasted malt aroma, smooth with a nice thick mouth feel, light carbonation, easy tasting chocolate malt flavor with roasted notes, nice smooth finish, enjoyable.

Pours a cloudy orange, off white head minimal and quickly dissipates, light caramel slightly sweet aroma, watery mouth feel, slight hit of hops on the finish, pretty tame taste wise not much to talk about a bit of citrus.

Draft, a dark black with lasting tan head, floral sweet roasted aroma with light carb just the right amount, very nice roasted malt flavor with a nice coffee finish, mediun body, this one surprised me I really enjoyed it.  Enjoyed it enough to have another one at the same sitting.

On draft at the Moon River Brew Pub cloudy amber color, with aspice and orange aroma, light white head not lasting, spice and metallic flavor, didnt do much for me expected more from it but it edged out the Captains Porter by a nose.

review_blob: Draft at the Moon River Brew Pub, poured adark brown with a tan head that quickly left the scene, roasted malt aroma, watery mouyth feel, metallic alcohol on the finish, with very light carbonation, expected a better beer than this when it arrived at the table.  Looks better than it tastes.
Pours, cloudy pale amber, 1/2 finger white head that disappears quickly, banana spice aroma and flavor, lightly carbonated, watery feel, citrus finish with a slight hops hit.

pours a honey color light white head that dissipates quickly, virtually no lacing, light malty aroma with a touch of sweetness, nice smooth tasting, malt with sweet toffee, nothing much to rave about a nice drink for a summers day.

Pours to a 2 finger tan head that lasted well with lacing, deep rich brown thats approaching black once its in the glass, malty aroma, smooth drinking, roasted coffee flavor come through, a bit of a sour finish
Two finger white head thats mostly lasting decent lacing, pours a golden color, malty with a slightly bitter hops finish, ok nothing special
